{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/shopify-remove-your-shop-name-from-the-website-title","result":{"pageContext":{"id":57,"date":"2020-10-28T09:17:04","date_gmt":"2020-10-28T09:17:04","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=57"},"modified":"2020-11-28T12:22:43","modified_gmt":"2020-11-28T12:22:43","slug":"shopify-remove-your-shop-name-from-the-website-title","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/shopify-remove-your-shop-name-from-the-website-title/","title":{"rendered":"Remove shop name from your Shopify store&#8217;s title"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Most Shopify themes automatically adds your store&#8217;s name to every single page at the end of the title for SEO. <br><br>However, depending on your SEO strategy, this can be an unwanted feature.  Fortunately it&#8217;s very simple to get that fixed.<br><br></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Editing the title in your theme&#8217;s code</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>In your Shopify Admin go to&nbsp;<strong>online store &gt; themes &gt; actions &gt; edit code</strong></li><li>In your&nbsp;<strong>theme.liquid file</strong>, find the<em>&lt;title&gt;</em>&nbsp;tag&nbsp;<em>(press CTRL + F or command + F on Mac to search)</em></li><li>Replace the entire line of the &lt;title&gt; tag with the following code:</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;title>{% if template contains \"index\" %}{{ page_title }}{% else %}{{ page_title }}{% if current_tags %} {{ 'general.meta.tagged_html' | t: tags: meta_tags }}{% endif %}{% if current_page != 1 %} {{ 'general.meta.page' | t: page_number: current_page }}{% endif %}{% endif %}&lt;/title></code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Every single page now won&#8217;t have your shop&#8217;s name at the end of the title. <br><br>Before:<br><br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"439\" height=\"161\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/image.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-65\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>After:<br><br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"380\" height=\"168\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-66\"/></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Although most Shopify themes automatically add your store&#8217;s name to the title it&#8217;s easy to get it removed.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":71,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[6,7],"image_alt":"Woman smiling while holding fairy lights.","featured_image_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/puravida-new-600x325.jpg","featured_image_small_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/puravida-new-100x100.jpg","post_count":2,"categories_names":["Blog"],"tag_names":["code","devtips"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/57"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/comments?post=57"}],"version-history":[{"count":9,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/57/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":76,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/57/revisions/76"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media/71"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media?parent=57"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/categories?post=57"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/tags?post=57"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}}},"staticQue